article.description: New Hampshire rolls past Lafayette in 45-7 rout
article.headline: New Hampshire rolls past Lafayette in 45-7 rout
article.linkText: New Hampshire rolls past Lafayette in 45-7 rout
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Sean Goldrich threw for 267 yards and two touchdowns and R.J. Harris had 173 yards receiving to help New Hampshire roll past Lafayette 45-7 Saturday and advance to the second round of the FCS playoffs. The Leopards (8-4, 6-2 Colonial Athletic Conference) jumped ahead quickly as Nico Steriti rushed for a one-yard score set up by a 39-yard pass from Goldrich to Harris. Goldrich threw two touchdowns to Harris and Dalton Crossan to grab a 21-0 advantage in the first quarter. Nick Cefalo had an 86-yard punt return touchdown the second quarter. Chris Setian and Crossan each added long scoring runs in the second half to fuel the rout. Lafayette (5-7, 4-1 Patriot League) got on the board late with a six-yard touchdown from Blake Searfoss to Mike Duncan. New Hampshire will face No. 5 seed Maine in the next round on Dec. 7.
